---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT } from '../site.config';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Privacy Policy',
  url: 'https://prosperityfederalsolutions.com/privacy/',
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy for the Prosperity Federal Solutions Site"
  description="How Prosperity Federal Solutions collects, uses, and protects the information you share with us."
  path="/privacy"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-gold">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="subhead">Effective Date: July 15, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container legal">
      <p>
        Prosperity Federal Solutions LLC ("Prosperity Federal Solutions," "we," "us," or "our")
        provides procurement, supply, and fulfillment solutions for government and institutional
        clients. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect through
        prosperityfederalsolutions.com (the "Site"), how we use it, and the choices available to
        you. By using the Site, you agree to the practices described in this Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Information you provide directly.</strong> When you submit our contact form,
          we collect your first name, last name, email address, and, if you choose to provide
          them, your phone number, agency or organization name, project description, and how you
          heard about us. Submitting a project description or contact details is voluntary, but
          required fields (name, email, and project description) are needed for us to respond.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>SMS opt-in.</strong> If you check the box on our contact form agreeing to
          receive text messages, we record that consent along with the phone number you provide.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Automatically collected information.</strong> We automatically collect
          technical information when you visit the Site, including your IP address, browser
          type, device type, referring URL, pages viewed, and time spent on the Site, through
          cookies and similar technologies described in Section 5.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Communications.</strong> If you contact us by phone, email, or by scheduling a
          consultation, we retain a record of that communication, including any information you
          voluntarily provide.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Create and maintain a contact record for you in our customer relationship
          management system (GoHighLevel, "GHL"), so we can respond to your inquiry and follow
          up appropriately;</li>
        <li>Evaluate and respond to federal, state, local, and institutional procurement
          inquiries submitted through the Site ("federal inquiry" data), including routing your
          message to the appropriate team member;</li>
        <li>Contact you by phone, text (if you have opted in), or email to discuss your
          procurement, supply, or fulfillment needs or to schedule a consultation;</li>
        <li>Improve the Site's content, usability, and performance; and</li>
        <li>Comply with applicable legal, regulatory, contractual, and recordkeeping
          obligations, including those that may apply to government procurement relationships.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Consent to Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you check the box on our contact form agreeing to receive text messages, or otherwise
        provide your telephone number, you consent to be contacted by Prosperity Federal
        Solutions LLC by telephone, text message (SMS), and email regarding your procurement
        inquiry and related services. Message and data rates may apply. Consent to be contacted
        is not a condition of engaging our services. You may revoke your consent at any time by
        replying "STOP" to any text message, clicking "unsubscribe" in any email, or contacting
        us using the information in Section 8.
      </p>

      <h2>4. How Your Contact Form Submission Is Handled</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit the contact form on this Site, your information is transmitted securely
        and used to automatically create or update a contact record in our GoHighLevel CRM. A
        member of our team then reviews your project description and reaches out using the
        contact method(s) you provided. A hidden "honeypot" field on the form helps us detect and
        block automated spam submissions; it is not visible to human visitors and no information
        entered into it (there should be none) is used for any purpose other than spam
        prevention.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies, pixels, and similar technologies to operate the Site, remember your
        preferences, measure traffic and engagement, and support analytics tools. You can control
        cookies through your browser settings; disabling cookies may affect certain Site
        functionality. We do not knowingly sell personal information, as that term is defined
        under applicable state privacy laws.
      </p>

      <h2>6. How We Share Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Service providers who help us operate the Site and manage contacts, including our
          CRM provider (GoHighLevel) and email/SMS delivery platforms, under confidentiality
          obligations;</li>
        <li>Subcontractors, suppliers, or partners only where necessary to evaluate or fulfill a
          procurement inquiry you have affirmatively made; and</li>
        <li>Government authorities or regulators, where required by law or applicable
          procurement regulations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Data Retention and Security</h2>
      <p>
        We retain contact and form information for as long as reasonably necessary to fulfill
        the purposes described in this Policy and to comply with applicable recordkeeping and
        contractual obligations. We use commercially reasonable administrative and technical
        safeguards to protect your information, but no method of transmission or storage is
        completely secure.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of the personal information we
        hold about you, or ask us to stop contacting you, by emailing {CONTACT.email} or calling
        {CONTACT.phone}. Depending on your state of residence, you may have additional rights
        under applicable privacy law.
      </p>

      <h2>9. No Guarantee of Contract Award</h2>
      <p>
        Information on this Site is provided for general informational purposes about our
        procurement, supply, and fulfillment capabilities. Submitting an inquiry through this
        Site does not constitute an offer, bid, proposal, or guarantee of any contract, award, or
        business relationship.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This Site is not directed to individuals under the age of 18, and we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Effective Date" above reflects
        the most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes
        acceptance of the updated Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this Privacy Policy may be directed to Prosperity Federal Solutions LLC
        at {CONTACT.email} or {CONTACT.phone}.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-dark) 0%, #2b1147 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .subhead { color: #e2d4f0; }
  .legal { max-width: 800px; }
  .legal h2 { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.3rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }
  .legal ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; }
</style>
